                                    <div class="row">
                                        <div class="serial">
                                            <span>Question 96 </span>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="questionText" style="display: block;">
                                            <p class="pt-000000e991d73e-8245-452a-bcb0-6ef12901e0c5" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><span xml:space="preserve" class="pt-000001e991d73e-8245-452a-bcb0-6ef12901e0c5">The speaker failed to make the audience </span><span xml:space="preserve" class="pt-000002e991d73e-8245-452a-bcb0-6ef12901e0c5">       </span><span xml:space="preserve" class="pt-000001e991d73e-8245-452a-bcb0-6ef12901e0c5"> to him patiently. Which of the following verb forms best completes the above sentence?</span><style>span { white-space: pre-wrap; }p.pt-000000e991d73e-8245-452a-bcb0-6ef12901e0c5 {line-height: 108%;margin-top: 0;margin-left: 0;margin-right: 0;margin-bottom: 0;}span.pt-000001e991d73e-8245-452a-bcb0-6ef12901e0c5 {font-family: Times New Roman;color: black;font-style: normal;font-weight: normal;margin: 0;padding: 0;}span.pt-000002e991d73e-8245-452a-bcb0-6ef12901e0c5 {font-family: Times New Roman;color: black;text-decoration: underline;font-style: normal;font-weight: normal;margin: 0;padding: 0;}</style></p>
